SIMPLE: pebble
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pebble
<hw>Peb"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>papolst⟦amac⟧n</ets>; cf. L. <ets>papula</ets> pimple, mote. See
<er>Stone</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small roundish piece of stone;
especially, a stone worn and rounded by the action of water; a
pebblestone.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>pebbles</xex> on the hungry
beach.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As children gathering <qex>pebbles</qex> on the shore.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Transparent and colorless rock crystal; <as>as,
Brazilian <ex>pebble</ex>; -- so called by opticians</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pebble powder</b></col>, <cd>slow-burning gunpowder, in
large cubical grains.</cd> -- <col><b>Scotch pebble</b></col>,
<cd>varieties of quartz, as agate, chalcedony, etc., obtained from
cavities in amygdaloid.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pebble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pebble
<hw>Peb"ble</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Pebbled</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pebbling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To grain (leather) so as to
produce a surface covered with small rounded prominences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pebbled</ent>⟦br⟧
